ike \u003cem\u003evarangue\u003c/em\u003e, a French term for the rib of a canoe that would rarely appear in the model’s training data, if ever. "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"7G4fXh","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"After much trial and error, he ended up with an AI assembly line using multiple models to sort documents, search them for keywords and meaning, and synthesize answers to queries. It took a lot of time and a lot of tinkering, but GPT helped teach him the Python he needed. He named the system HistoryPearl, after his smartest cat. "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"gjjCYY","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"He tested his system against edge cases, like the Norwegian trader Ferdinand Wentzel, who wrote about himself in the third person and deployed an odd sense of humor, for example, writing about the birth of his son by speculating about his paternity and making self-deprecating jokes about his own height — “F. W.’s Girl was safely delivered of a boy. - I almost believe it is his Son for his features seem to bear some resemblance of him \u0026amp; his short legs seem to determine this opinion beyond doubt.” This sort of writing stymied earlier models, but HistoryPearl could pull it up in response to a vaguely phrased question about Wentzel’s humor, along with other examples of Wentzel’s wit Humphries hadn’t been looking for. "},"dropcap":false,"endmark":false,"lead":false},{"__typename":"EntryBodyParagraph","placement":{"id":"tWCF6B","alignment":null},"__isEntryBodyComponent":"EntryBodyParagraph","contents":{"html":"The tool still missed some things, but it performed better than the average graduate student Humphries would normally hire to do this sort of work. And faster. And much, much cheaper. Last November, after Open